<li>NAT traversal techniques like UDP hole-punching enable 70% direct connectivity, with relay fallback ensuring universal reachability.</li>
<li>WireGuard offers efficient, simple, kernel-level encryption, ideal for resource-constrained and containerized agent deployments.</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p>AI agent networks no longer live inside a single data center. They span AWS, GCP, Azure, and edge nodes simultaneously, crossing NAT boundaries and untrusted networks with every message. Securing those peer-to-peer communications is critical, and encrypted tunnels are the foundational building block that makes it practical. This article breaks down the core security, operational, performance, and implementation advantages of encrypted tunnels for decentralized agent systems, so you can make informed architecture decisions backed by evidence.</p>
